&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Last of All Suns,&lt;/span&gt; by John C.Wright&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Unnoted Abridgements&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have been informed that the following editions of &lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Night Land&lt;/span&gt; are abridged, but the abridgement is not noted in the book descriptions online, or on the covers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Night Land: A Love Tale (The Radium Age Science Fiction Series)&lt;/span&gt; published by HiLoBooks. Apparently Mr. Hodgson's original ending has been omitted — which dramatically changes the work (not, in my opinion, for the better).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Night Land,&lt;/span&gt; Volumes I and II, published by Pan/Ballantine, with an introduction by Lin Carter.&lt;/li&gt;
